## Summary

**What changed:**
• `scripts/task_manifest.py` line 313: Added `task.get("files")` as the first condition in the `selectable` filter, rejecting tasks with empty `Files:` entries before they reach implementation selection.
• `scripts/test_task_manifest.py`: Added two tests (108 lines):
  • `test_manifest_excludes_file_less_tasks_from_selectable` — verifies file-less task is warned + excluded while a sibling task with files is still selected.
  • `test_manifest_no_selectable_when_all_file_less` — verifies `no_selectable_tasks` warning fires when all candidates have no files.

**Verification:** All 22 tests pass (`python3 -m unittest scripts.test_task_manifest`).

**Effect:** Tasks with empty `Files:` entries now fail at the planning/manifest stage (cheap) instead of burning a full implementation session that ends in scope-mismatch reversion. This addresses Issue #79.

